1.title: The Wild Hunt
1.plot: A fierce creature is terrorizing the Candy Kingdom but before Finn can slay the beast, he must first overcome a guilty conscience.

2.title: Always BMO Closing
2.plot: BMO and Ice King hit the road as door-to-door salesmen and stumble upon an irresistible opportunity.

3.title: Son of Rap Bear
3.plot: When Flame Princess is coaxed into a high stakes battle against the indomitable Son of Rap Bear, Finn must help her search for a new strategy.

4.title: Bonnibel Bubblegum
4.plot: A long lost artifact causes Princess Bubblegum to go back to the creation of the Candy Kingdom.

5.title: Seventeen
5.plot: A mysterious knight crashes Finn's birthday bash and presents him with a dangerous gift.

6.title: Ring of Fire
6.plot: When an old flame comes calling on urgent business, Tree Trunks reconsiders both her wild past and her tranquil present.

7.title: Marcy & Hunson
7.plot: After helping with the creation of a new sword, Hunson Abadeer comes back to try and regain her daughter's love.

8.title: The First Investigation
8.plot: Finn and Jake are tasked with investigating reports of a haunting at Joshua and Margaret's old office.

9.title: Blenanas
9.plot: Finn's latest literary work meets with only derision, so he sets out to prove all the naysayers wrong.

10.title: Jake the Starchild
10.plot: In order to fulfill his grand destiny, Jake is spirited away by a strangely familiar shape-shifting alien.

11.title: Temple of Mars
11.plot: Searching for answers on Mars, Finn and Jermaine discover that they must first survive a cunning Martian mental trap.

12.title: Gumbaldia
12.plot: Finn and Jake, as ambassadors of the Candy Kingdom, travel to a powerful new city-state in a last ditch effort to stave off war.

13.title: Come Along With Me
13.plot: BMO narrates "The Great Gum War" in which Finn, Jake, Marceline, PB and the Candy Kingdom go to war against Gumbald and his army that will determine the fate of Ooo once and for all.

1.title: Slumber Party Panic
1.plot: Princess Bumblegum's latest experiment accidentally unleashes an undead horde upon the Candy Kingdom.

2.title: Trouble in Lumpy Space
2.plot: Jake is bitten by Lumpy Space Princess and begins to transform into a Lumpy being. In order to find a cure, Finn is travels to Lumpy Space.

3.title: Prisoners of Love
3.plot: After the Ice King kidnaps a large group of princesses, its up to Finn and Jake to free them.

4.title: Tree Trunks
4.plot: Tree Trunks joins Finn and Jake on an quest, but finds her talents for adventuring leave something to be desired.

5.title: The Enchiridion!
5.plot: Princess Bubblegum sends Finn on his most challenging quest yet--to recover The Enchiridion, the hero's handbook.

6.title: The Jiggler
6.plot: After finding a Jiggler in the wild, Finn and Jake decide to adopt the funny creature as a pet.

7.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
7.plot: A new stranger arrives in the Candy Kingdom: a charismatic talking heart named Ricardio. He soon becomes very popular, except to Finn who believes he's hiding something.

8.title: Business Time
8.plot: Finn and Jake discover a tribe of businessmen frozen in a block of ice and hire them to make adventuring easier.

9.title: My Two Favorite People
9.plot: Jake tries hanging out with both his best friend, Finn, and his girlfriend, Lady Rainicorn, at the same time. But soon Jake becomes jealous when Finn and Lady seem too friendly.

10.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
10.plot: While having trouble solving the contradictory problems of the residents of a mountain village, Finn recalls where he found the desire to help people.

11.title: Wizard
11.plot: Finn and Jake discover a secret tribe of wizards and take magic lessons for a price they aren't prepared to pay.

12.title: Evicted!
12.plot: After Marceline the Vampire Queen visits Finn and Jake at their tree fort she informs them that she is moving in and kicking them out.

13.title: City of Thieves
13.plot: A mission leads Jake into a city where everyone is a thief and the chance to be corrupted is incredibly strong.

14.title: The Witch's Garden
14.plot: A witch steals Jake's shape-shifting powers, but his ego makes getting them back very difficult.

15.title: What Is Life?
15.plot: Finn creates a robot to continuously throw pies at Jake but unexpectedly imbues it with a soul.

16.title: Ocean of Fear
16.plot: Finn must overcome his fear of the ocean.

17.title: When Wedding Bells Thaw
17.plot: The Ice King announces that he is engaged and to the shock of Finn and Jake it seems the bride is actually willing. But will the Ice King give up his princess kidnapping ways?

18.title: Dungeon
18.plot: Finn adventures into a forbidden dungeon, against the wishes of Princess Bumblegum and Jake, and finds more than he bargained for.

19.title: The Duke
19.plot: An accident in the Candy Kingdom which Finn and Jake cause is blamed on the Duke of Nuts. Finn and Jake, however, find admitting the truth to be harder and harder as time passes.

20.title: Freak City
20.plot: A trickster turns Finn into a giant foot.

21.title: Donny
21.plot: Finn and Jake try to reform a bullying ogre, but realize that their good deed has unexpected consequences.

22.title: Henchman
22.plot: Marceline the Vampire Queen tricks Finn into swearing allegiance to her.

23.title: Rainy Day Daydream
23.plot: Jake's imagination literally runs wild, coming to life and bringing many dangers into the tree house.

24.title: What Have You Done?
24.plot: After being told to arrest the Ice King, Finn and Jake face an ethical quandary when they realize the villain has not actually committed any recent crimes.

25.title: His Hero
25.plot: Finn meets his hero, the great warrior Billy, who is not everything Finn expected him to be.

26.title: Gut Grinder
26.plot: Jake is accused of being a horrible monster that has been terrorizing the locals. Soon, Jake himself is unsure if he is or isn't the monster.

1.title: It Came from the Nightosphere
1.plot: Finn summons the Lord of Evil to reconcile with his daughter, Marceline the Vampire Queen, but ends up unleashing him of the unsuspecting land.

2.title: The Eyes
2.plot: Because of a creepy horse outside their window, Finn and Jake cannot get any sleep.

3.title: Loyalty to the King
3.plot: After shaving, the Ice King is mistaken as a good guy and takes advantage of the situation.

4.title: Blood Under the Skin
4.plot: Finn is made fun of by a group of knights and reacts by questing for a set of magical armor that will earn him respect.

5.title: Storytelling
5.plot: Unable to give a sick Jake an entertaining story, Finn sets off into the woods to discover a true story.

6.title: Slow Love
6.plot: Finn and Jake try to find a girlfriend for a giant snail so that it will stop wrecking their tree-house.

7.title: Power Animal
7.plot: Finn is kidnapped, but Jake's short attention span means rescue is dubious.

8.title: Crystals Have Power
8.plot: Jake swears a life of non-violence right before a race of indestructible crystal-men abduct Finn to another dimension.

9.title: The Other Tarts
9.plot: Finn and Jake are given one of the highest responsibilities: transporting and guarding the rarest pastry in the Candy Kingdom.

10.title: To Cut a Woman's Hair
10.plot: An evil witch threatens to crush Jake to death if Finn doesn't deliver her the hair of a princess.

11.title: The Chamber of Frozen Blades
11.plot: While he's away, Finn and Jake sneak into Ice King's fortress.

12.title: Her Parents
12.plot: Anxious about meeting Lady Rainicorn's parents, Jake tries to pass himself off as a Rainicorn.

13.title: The Pods
13.plot: Given the duty of protecting three magic beans, one evil and two good, Finn and Jake decide to plant them to find out which is which.

14.title: The Silent King
14.plot: After defeating their king, Finn becomes the new ruler of the Goblin people, and finds that their strange ways are too difficult to understand.

15.title: The Real You
15.plot: Nervous about giving a speech at Princess Bubblegum's science conference and barbecue, Finn finds a magical pair of glasses that make him the smartest being in the land.

16.title: Guardians of Sunshine
16.plot: Finn and Jake become trapped inside one of BMO's video game creations.

17.title: Death in Bloom
17.plot: After accidentally killing Princess Bubblegum's beloved plant, Finn and Jake travel to the land of the dead to bring it back to life.

18.title: Susan Strong
18.plot: Having always believed he is the only human left in the Land of Ooo, Finn believes he has discovered a tribe to primitive humans living underground.

19.title: Mystery Train
19.plot: While traveling on a train, Finn and Jake find themselves in the middle of a murder mystery.

20.title: Go with Me
20.plot: Jake and Marceline give Finn conflicting advise on how to ask out Princess Bubblegum.

21.title: Belly of the Beast
21.plot: Finn and Jake must save a group of clueless, party-minded teddy bears living inside the belly of a monster.

22.title: The Limit
22.plot: An enormous maze tests the limit of Jake's stretching power.

23.title: Video Makers
23.plot: Finn and Jake set out to make their own movie, but have conflicting visions of what their movie should be.

24.title: Mortal Folly
24.plot: The Lich, the greatest form of pure evil in the land of Ooo, is accidentally unleashed. With the highest stakes, Finn and Jake set out on the most serious adventure of their career.

25.title: Mortal Recoil
25.plot: With the evil Lich seemingly defeated, Finn and Jake are uneasy with their success because of its great cost.

26.title: Heat Signature
26.plot: Finn and Jake ask Marceline the Vampire Queen to turn them into vampires. However, she isn't interested in transforming her friends and tricks them into thinking she has.

1.title: Conquest of Cuteness
1.plot: Finn and Jake come under attack in their home from a race of super-evil creatures which are too cute to be taken seriously.

2.title: Morituri Te Salutamus
2.plot: Finn and Jake end up in a haunted arena where they must fight ghost gladiators to escape.

3.title: Memory of a Memory
3.plot: Finding their friend, Marceline the Vampire Queen, in a deep sleep, a mysterious stranger helps Finn and Jake by sending them into her dreams to awaken her.

4.title: Hitman
4.plot: The Ice King looks to hire a professional bully to beat up Finn and Jake, but inadvertently hires a deadly, unstoppable contract killer.

5.title: Too Young
5.plot: Finn is happy that Princess Bubblegum has regressed to the same age as him. But soon a challenger for the throne arrives to unseat the newly underage princess.

6.title: The Monster
6.plot: The king and queen of Lumpy Space ask Finn to find and return Lumpy Space Princess, who has been living in the woods and mistaken as a monster.

7.title: Still
7.plot: The Ice King uses a potion that paralyzes Finn and Jake, who become the lonely villain's unwilling best friends.

8.title: Wizard Battle
8.plot: The Ice King enters a battle of wizards from all over the Land of Ooo, to win a kiss from Princess Bubblegum--which Finn and Jake look to prevent.

9.title: Fionna and Cake
9.plot: In a world where all the characters are different genders, the adventurer Fionna gets advice from her cat-friend Cake on her date with Prince Gumball.

10.title: What Was Missing
10.plot: In order to open a magic door filled with stolen items, Finn and all his friends must perform in a band. But everyone's differing musical tastes and overall tensions make things difficult.

11.title: Apple Thief
11.plot: After Tree Trunks finds her apples have gone missing, Finn and Jake search the criminal underworld of the Candy Kingdom to recover them.

12.title: The Creeps
12.plot: Finn's masquerade birthday party turns into a deadly mystery.

13.title: From Bad to Worse
13.plot: The undead plague returns to the Candy Kingdom.

14.title: Beautopia
14.plot: Susan Strong returns and asks Finn and Jake to save her people from the Glubs. But Finn is still not sure if he can trust her after last time.

15.title: No One Can Hear You
15.plot: After trying to stop a deer that has been licking the Candy Kingdom people, Finn wakes up in a hospital to find everyone missing expect Jake who is acting very strange.

16.title: Jake vs. Me-Mow
16.plot: A tiny cat assassin tries to black mail Jake into killing someone, by hiding in his nose with some poison.

17.title: Thank You
17.plot: A fire-breathing wolf cub becomes lost in the snowy woods and becomes unlikely friends with a tall snow-creature.

18.title: The New Frontier
18.plot: Jake has a dream that seems to foretell his death but, to Finn's dismay, doesn't take it serious.

19.title: Holly Jolly Secrets
19.plot: In Finn and Jake's holiday special, the heroes come across a video diary of the Ice King's and attempt to decipher its secrets.

20.title: Holly Jolly Secrets
20.plot: In part two of the holiday special, The Ice King tries to get his video diary back from Finn and Jake.

21.title: Marceline's Closet
21.plot: Bored waiting for her, Finn and Jake sneak into Marceline's house, become trapped when she comes home, and witness her strange behavior when she's alone.

22.title: Paper Pete
22.plot: A secret war takes place in the library between tiny paper people and mold creatures, and Finn is brought into the middle of it all.

23.title: Another Way
23.plot: Finn journeys for a cyclops's magical tears to cure his injuries, but have trouble because of his stubborn inability to follow the advice of others.

24.title: Ghost Princess
24.plot: Finn and Jake try to help Ghost Princess by solving her murder.

25.title: Dad's Dungeon
25.plot: Finn and Jake discover a lost message from their dad which sends them to a mysterious and dangerous dungeon.

26.title: Incendium
26.plot: Trying to help Finn get over his hopeless feelings for Princess Bubblegum, Jake sets out to find a new princess for Finn to go out with.

1.title: Hot to the Touch
1.plot: Refusing to believe that she is evil, Finn tries to win over his new crush, Flame Princess.

2.title: Five Short Graybles
2.plot: Five short stories of Finn, Jake and their friends.

3.title: Web Weirdos
3.plot: After being caught by a giant spider, Finn and Jake try and help the arachnid with its marital problems so they won't be eaten.

4.title: Dream of Love
4.plot: Tree Trunks finds love but her public displays of affection nauseate everyone around her.

5.title: Return to the Nightosphere
5.plot: Finn and Jake find themselves imprisoned in the dark realm of the Nightosphere with no memory of how they came to be there.

6.title: Daddy's Little Monster
6.plot: Continuing their mysterious quest in the Nightosphere, Finn and Jake must rescue their friend Marceline the Vampire Queen.

7.title: In Your Footsteps
7.plot: A cute, bumbling bear begins to follow and mimic Finn. At first Finn enjoys having the furry admirer, but soon becomes uneasy with the bear's devotion.

8.title: Hug Wolf
8.plot: A Hug Wolf, a monstrous wolf that gives hugs against the will of its victims, turns Finn into one of its kind.

9.title: Princess Monster Wife
9.plot: The Ice King steals various body parts from all the princesses to construct his own perfect princess bride.

10.title: Goliad
10.plot: Princess Bubblegum uses her own DNA to create an intelligent and immortal sphinx which is planned to one day succeed her to the throne, except that Finn and Jake accidentally affect those plans.

11.title: Beyond This Earthly Realm
11.plot: A magic curse turns Finn into a ghost, invisible to everyone but the Ice King.

12.title: Gotcha!
12.plot: Lumpy Space Princess sets out to write a book on how to catch a man and goes undercover as Finn and Jake's secretary in order to seduce Finn.

13.title: Princess Cookie
13.plot: The Candy Kingdom faces a hostage crisis from a cookie that demands Princess Bubblegum's crown.

14.title: Card Wars
14.plot: As Finn joins in on Jake's favorite, hyper-complicated card game, emotions and poor gamesmanship run high.

15.title: Sons of Mars
15.plot: Magic Man switches bodies with Jake so that he can escape his trial on Mars, leaving it up to Finn to reveal the truth and save his friend.

16.title: Burning Low
16.plot: Finn and Flame Princess cautiously begin a relationship as boyfriend and girlfriend, of which Princess Bubblegum disapproves.

17.title: BMO Noire
17.plot: BMO uses hard-boiled detective skills to locate Finn's missing sock.

18.title: King Worm
18.plot: Finn finds himself trapped in a bizarre dream, the outcome of which may determine if he ever wakes up.

19.title: Lady & Peebles
19.plot: Princess Bubblegum and Lady Rainicorn must rescue Finn and Jake.

20.title: You Made Me
20.plot: The would-be usurper to the throne, Lemongrab, returns to the Candy Kingdom, demanding volunteer subjects for his own kingdom.

21.title: Who Would Win
21.plot: While training for an epic battle, Finn and Jake take their frustrations out in a fight against each other.

22.title: Ignition Point
22.plot: Finn and Jake sneak into the Fire Kingdom to retrieve some of Flame Princess' things, and stumble onto a plot to kill the Flame King.

23.title: The Hard Easy
23.plot: A tribe of swamp creatures ask Finn and Jake to save them from a Mega Frog.

24.title: Reign of Gunters
24.plot: While the Ice King is away, his sidekick Gunther the penguin uses a magic amulet to conquer the countryside and attack the Candy Kingdom.

25.title: I Remember You
25.plot: The Ice King asks Marcelline the Vampire Queen to help him write a song.

26.title: The Lich
26.plot: Finn has an unclear premonition involving The Lich and sets out to stop the undead creature.

1.title: Finn the Human
1.plot: Finn's wish to stop the evil Lich has massive cosmic consequences.

2.title: Jake the Dog
2.plot: Following the unexpected consequences of Finn's cosmic wish it's up to the Jake -- and his short attention span -- to set things right.

3.title: Five More Short Graybles
3.plot: Five more short stories with one connecting theme.

4.title: Up a Tree
4.plot: Having been magical shrunk to the size of a forest animal, Finn takes up a quest to climb a tree and retrieve his lost flying disc.

5.title: All the Little People
5.plot: Finn receives a mysterious bag that contains what appears to be living toys of everyone he knows, which playing with has unexpected results.

6.title: Jake the Dad
6.plot: Lady gives birth to a litter of puppies and Jake becomes an eager but frantic father.

7.title: Davey
7.plot: Finn becomes Davey, an alter-ego, everyman in order to escape the attention of fame and becomes consumed by his new identity.

8.title: Mystery Dungeon
8.plot: Ice King, Neptr, Tree Trunks, Shelby and Lemongrab wake up in a dungeon and must work together to escape.

9.title: All Your Fault
9.plot: Lemongrab sends a distress message to the Candy Kingdom which Finn and Jake respond to.

11.title: Bad Little Boy
11.plot: A return to the gender-swapped world with Fionna and Cake and Marshall Lee the Vampire King.

12.title: Vault of Bones
12.plot: Finn and Flame Princess explore a dungeon together.

13.title: The Great Bird Man
13.plot: Finn and Jake get lost in the badlands and are saved by Xergiok, ex-Goblin King who now lives in a cave. A look at what Ice King and Marceline were like 996 years ago.

14.title: Simon & Marcy
14.plot: Marceline tells Finn and Jake about her and Ice King's past, 996 years ago.

15.title: A Glitch Is a Glitch
15.plot: Ice King creates a computer virus to delete everybody except him and Princess Bubblegum. Stuck inside the treehouse during a sword storm, Jake builds a pillow fort while Finn goes to a different world.

16.title: Puhoy
16.plot: Depressed by his feelings with Flame Princess, Finn enters a pillow fort where he enters a new world and makes a new life for himself.

17.title: BMO Lost
17.plot: BMO gets snatched away by a giant eagle and must find his way home.

18.title: Princess Potluck
18.plot: Ice King does everything possible to ruin a princess potluck he believes he didn't get invited to.

19.title: James Baxter the Horse
19.plot: Finn and Jake meet a horse with the power to make sad people happy.

20.title: Shh!
20.plot: Finn and Jake hold a contest to see who can last longer without talking.

21.title: The Suitor
21.plot: Peppermint Butler thinks Princess Bubblegum is spending too much time in her lab and decides she needs a suitor.

22.title: The Party's Over, Isla de Señorita
22.plot: After becoming tired of always losing to Finn and Jake and failing to win Princess Bubblegum's love, Ice King decides to throw in the towel.

23.title: One Last Job
23.plot: Jake Jr. gets mixed up with some bad eggs, and Jake reunites with his old gang to save her.

24.title: Another Five More Short Graybles
24.plot: Five short stories, some involving Finn and Jake building a time machine.

25.title: Candy Streets
25.plot: Lumpy Space Princess is robbed and faints before she can tell Finn and Jake who robbed her.

26.title: Wizards Only, Fools
26.plot: Princess Bubblegum believes magic is nothing but a bunch of hooey until Starchy gets sick.

27.title: Jakesuit
27.plot: Jake is sick and tired of Finn using his body as a suit of armor.

28.title: Be More
28.plot: Finn and Jake disguise themselves as MOs in order to infiltrate the MO factory.

29.title: Sky Witch
29.plot: Princess Bubblegum and Marceline team up to reclaim lost property.

30.title: Frost & Fire
30.plot: After Flame Princess battles Ice King, Finn has an exciting dream.

31.title: Too Old
31.plot: Finn and Princess Bubblegum discover a talented lemon citizen named Lemonhope while on a diplomatic trip to Castle Lemongrab; also, something strange is happening to the Earls of Lemongrab, leading to their society crumbling.

32.title: Earth & Water
32.plot: Princess Bubblegum subjects Flame Princess to a series of tests to gauge Fire Princess' fiery tendencies.

33.title: Time Sandwich
33.plot: Jake crafts the most delicious sandwich ever.

34.title: The Vault
34.plot: Jake and BMO help Finn tap into his repressed memories to uncover a secret past.

35.title: Love Games
35.plot: Slime Princess needs a husband or else she'll lose the Slime Kingdom to her obnoxious sister.

36.title: Dungeon Train
36.plot: Finn and Jake discover a train where every car is a dungeon filled with a new foe for Finn to fight.

37.title: Box Prince
37.plot: Finn meets the Box Prince (a cat with a box on its back) and discovers the Box Kingdom has been taken over by an impostor.

38.title: Red Starved
38.plot: Finn, Jake and Marceline become trapped underground. Starving for anything red Marceline begins to loose control and turns her eyes to Finn and Jake's blood.

39.title: We Fixed a Truck
39.plot: Finn and Jake find a broken down pickup truck and enlist the help of BMO and Banana Man to fix it.

40.title: Play Date
40.plot: Sick and tired of babysitting Ice King while the Ice Kingdom is being rebuilt, Finn and Jake call up an old friend to hang out with their annoying houseguest: Abracadaniel. But when Ice King and his new BFF accidentally unleash the demon Kee-Oth, Finn and Jake have to clean up their mess.

41.title: The Pit
41.plot: Kee-Oth the Blood Demon has kidnapped Jake, taken him back to his dimension and thrown him in a pit. If Finn wants to rescue his friend, he's going to need Lady Rainicorn's help... and a videotape that will reveal how to open the portal to Kee-Oth's messed-up dimension.

42.title: James
42.plot: Finn and Jake accompany Princess Bubblegum on her study of the Desert of Wonders. However, they are soon attacked by goo monsters, and Finn and Jake think that Bubblegum's robot helper James is to blame.

43.title: Root Beer Guy
43.plot: Root beer guy must put aside his common everyday life to search for the truth behind the murders, lies, and deceit in the Candy Kingdom.

44.title: Apple Wedding
44.plot: Tree Trunks and Mr. Pig are getting married.

46.title: Rattleballs
46.plot: Finn meets an old robot in the junkyard who promises to make Finn into a master swordsman.

47.title: The Red Throne
47.plot: The Fire King and Don John the Flame Lord take over the Fire Kingdom. Now Flame Princess must use Finn's and Cinnamon Bun's help to get it back.

48.title: Betty
48.plot: The Ice King loses his powers, reverts to his old human-self, and begins to wither away due to being over a thousand years old.

49.title: Bad Timing
49.plot: Bubblegum Princess invents a time travel sphere that Lumpy Space Princess wants for solving her relationship problems.

50.title: Lemonhope Part One
50.plot: Young Lemonhope leaves the candy kingdom after a deep desire to be free of all responsibilities grips him. So he ventures out on his own with nothing more than a lute and hope to find freedom.

51.title: Lemonhope Part Two
51.plot: Lemonhope meets an adventurer who teaches him true freedom. But even with his new life of freedom he is plagued with dreams of his lemon kingdom and his family being imprisoned.

52.title: Billy's Bucket List
52.plot: Finn meets Billy's ex-girlfriend, Canyon, who finds Billy's bucket list. Finn vows to complete it for his late hero.

1.title: Wake Up
1.plot: Finn tracks down who he believes is his father.

2.title: Escape from the Citadel
2.plot: Finn finds his long-lost father after following the Lich to the Citadel. As it turns out, maybe this wasn't such a good idea?

3.title: James II
3.plot: 'James', Finn & Jake, and Princess Bubblegum discover that James has been cloned 25 times, and that the original zombie James is returning - and not in a good way.

4.title: The Tower
4.plot: Finn decides to build a tower to space.

5.title: Sad Face
5.plot: Once a month, while Finn and Jake are asleep, Jake's tail comes to life. It travels to a little circus in the forest, where it is known as Blue Nose the sad faced clown. But Blue Nose and the ringmaster come to a disagreement regarding the treatment of the "beast" Goralina.

6.title: Breezy
6.plot: In an attempt to help his wilting arm-flower, Finn begins a search for smooches with the help of a friendly bee named Breezy.

7.title: Food Chain
7.plot: Finn and Jake learn how the food chain works with a little help from Magic Man.

8.title: Furniture & Meat
8.plot: Finn and Jake spend all their money.

9.title: The Prince Who Wanted Everything
9.plot: Back to the Fiona and Cake universe when LSP wants the Ice King to tell (her) version of Lumpy Space Prince's life, but she has an ulterior motive.

10.title: Something Big
10.plot: The Sky Witch attacks the Candy Kingdom.

11.title: Little Brother
11.plot: Shelby gains a little brother who sets off to battle.

12.title: Ocarina
12.plot: Kim Kil Whan wants to teach his dad Jake responsibility.

13.title: Thanks for the Crabapples, Giuseppe!
13.plot: Ice King goes on a spiritual journey.

14.title: Princess Day
14.plot: Marceline and Lumpy Space Princess cause chaos at the Breakfast Kingdom.

15.title: Nemesis
15.plot: A crusader against the dark arts seeks to banish Peppermint Butler.

16.title: Joshua & Margaret Investigations
16.plot: Jake tells the story of his and his brother Jermaine's' births.

17.title: Ghost Fly
17.plot: Jake kills a fly that gets into his soup. However, he and Finn must get creative when the fly returns as a powerful ghost to haunt them.

18.title: Everything's Jake
18.plot: Jake is transported to a different world.

19.title: Is That You?
19.plot: After the death of Prismo, Finn and Jake do a funeral ritual. But when Jake eats the last pickle of the jar of pickles that Prismo made for him, he is transported to Prismo's lair. Will Finn be able to save him?

20.title: Jake the Brick
20.plot: Jake is conducting an experiment of being a brick in a brick-shack.

21.title: Dentist
21.plot: Finn has a toothache, so he has to go to the dentist.

22.title: The Cooler
22.plot: Flame Princess asks Princess Bubblegum for help when her city is cooled down.

23.title: The Pajama War
23.plot: A slumber party is being held in the Candy Kingdom and Finn and Princess Bubblegum are sent to 7 minutes in Heaven.

24.title: Evergreen
24.plot: Set in the Prehistoric Era, Evergreen and his aprentice Gunter have to stop a meteor heading towards Earth.

25.title: Astral Plane
25.plot: Finn and Jake go camping in the woods. When they go to sleep, Finn has an out-of-body experience and visits other creatures all around Ooo while he slowly ascends to space.

26.title: Gold Stars
26.plot: During his first day of school, Sweet Pea is approached by the King of OOO and his companion, Toronto, who lure him into dancing in public.

27.title: The Visitor
27.plot: Finn's dream about following a comet to its crash site reunites him with an old friend.

28.title: The Mountain
